ENTRY            A0920   20260207   20260508   20260508       A132
SUBENT        A0920001   20260207   20260508   20260508       A132
BIB                 14         45
TITLE      Investigation of the 243Am + 48Ca reaction products
           previously observed in the experiments on elements
           113, 115 and 117.
AUTHOR     (Yu.Ts.Oganessian, F.Sh.Abdullin, S.N.Dmitriev,
           J.M.Gostic, J.H.Hamilton, R.A.Henderson, M.G.Itkis,
           K.J.Moody, A.N.Polyakov, A.V.Ramayya, J.B.Roberto,
           K.P.Rykaczewski, R.N.Sagaidak, D.A.Shaughnessy,
           I.V.Shirokovsky, M.A.Stoyer, N.J.Stoyer, V.G.Subbotin,
           A.M.Sukhov, Yu.S.Tsyganov, V.K.Utyonkov, A.A.Voinov,
           G.K.Vostokin)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,87,014302,2013) final results
           (J,PRL,108,022502,2012)
REL-REF    (N,A0890002,Yu.Ts.Oganessian+,J,PR/C,72,034611,2005)
           AM-243(20-CA-48,4N), AM-243(20-CA-48,3N) reported
           (R,,G.Audi+,J,NP/A,729,337,2003) for mass
COMMENT    *By author*. Excitation energies of the compound nuclei
           are calculated using the masses found in REL-REF.
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB,1USALRL,1USAVBT,1USAORL)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,4ZZZDUB) U-400 Cyclotron and the Dubna
           gas-filled recoil separator.
METHOD     (TOF)
PART-DET   (A) And residual nuclides.
SAMPLE     The 0.37-mg/cm2 rotating targets of Am-243 (99.5-99.9%)
           deposited onto 1.5-um Ti foils.
           When determining cross sections in the experiments
           with the 0.68 and 0.84 mg/cm2 targets,we corrected the
           separator's transmission for increased scattering
           losses in the target. In calculations of the cross
           sections in both these cases we used 35% or the
           effective target thickness of 0.4 mg/cm2.
DETECTOR   (MCPLT) A 4-cm x 12-cm semiconductor detector array
           with 12 vertical position-sensitive strips surrounded
           by eight 4-cm x 4-cm side detectors without position
           sensitivity, forming a box open to the front (beam)
           side. The position-averaged detection efficiency for
           full-energy alpha-particles emitted in the decays of
           implanted nuclei was 87%.
MISC-COL   (MISC) The excitation energy of the compound nucleus.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainties
HISTORY    (20120119C) SB
           (20130205R) Data were received from Dr.V.Utyonkov
           (20130205A) Entry was re-compiled- new papers with
           final table data were received
           (20170211A) SD:REACTION code updated in Subents 002-004
           (20260207U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              45
